To help you discover if your contacts are WhatsApp users when you choose to sync your device’s address book and manage your contacts on WhatsApp using contact upload, we:
regularly identify other WhatsApp users in your address book, add them to your WhatsApp contact list and store cryptographic hash values of the phone numbers of your contacts who are
not WhatsApp users
, so we can quickly update your WhatsApp contacts if those contacts sign-up to WhatsApp at a later date.
securely save your contacts on WhatsApp to allow you to manage them on linked devices and restore them on any device. Learn more
here
.
remove contacts from your WhatsApp contact list if one of your contacts no longer has an account.
at your request, block phone numbers of other users to prevent them contacting you on WhatsApp.
